<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910411-0036</DOCNO><DOCID>910411-0036.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Reading andamp; Bates Corp.:   New York Investment Firm   Puts 2 Directors on Board</HL><DATE>04/11/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   RB WNEWS</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)</MS><IN>OIL DRILLING AND EXPLORATION (DRL)OIL EQUIPMENT AND SERVICES (OIE)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><NS>PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS, PROMOTIONS, APPOINTMENTS (PER)</NS><RE>TEXAS (TX)</RE><LP>   A New York investment concern placed two directors on theboard of Reading andamp; Bates Corp. and said it may seek to doublethe number to four.   WHR Management Co., the general partner of Randamp;B InvestmentPartnership L.P., holds a 24% stake in Reading andamp; Bates,acquired in a recent recapitalization of the Houston offshoredrilling and engineering services company.</LP><TEXT>   Yesterday, Reading andamp; Bates said it named four newdirectors, for a total of 11, including two representing WHR.&quot;We may or may not seek additional seats,&quot; said C. Kirk RheinJr., a WHR general partner who was named to the Reading andamp;Bates board.   The investors disclosed their interest in acquiring moreboard seats in a 13D filing with the Securities and ExchangeCommission. Reading andamp; Bates declined comment on the filing.   Ted Kalborg, who is also affiliated with WHR and is asenior partner and managing director of Tufton Associates,London, was named to the Reading andamp; Bates board as well.</TEXT></DOC>